WEBVTT

00:07.833 --> 00:10.833
[playing rock music]

00:10.833 --> 00:15.300
*

00:15.300 --> 00:17.867
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
hold up, hold up, hold up.

00:17.867 --> 00:20.200
If we're gonna win
Battle of the Bands,

00:20.200 --> 00:22.233
we got to rock
that stage.

00:22.233 --> 00:24.567
It's all about showmanship.

00:24.567 --> 00:27.900
Ladies and gentlemen,
Freddy on the drums!

00:27.900 --> 00:30.167
[all cheering]

00:30.167 --> 00:31.500
- Yeah.

00:31.500 --> 00:34.167
- I love it.
Lawrence on the keys!

00:34.167 --> 00:35.600
[all cheering]

00:35.600 --> 00:38.033
- Yeah.
Yeah.

00:38.033 --> 00:40.367
Oh! Ho ho ho!

00:40.367 --> 00:43.267
Lawrence von Butthoven.

00:43.267 --> 00:45.900
Tomika, rock out
front and center!

00:45.900 --> 00:46.900
[all cheering]
- [playing bass]

00:46.900 --> 00:48.733
- Tomika!

00:48.733 --> 00:50.067
Tomika.

00:50.067 --> 00:51.400
[playing bass]

00:51.400 --> 00:54.233
Or rock out crouched
behind that speaker.

00:54.233 --> 00:56.467
- Mm!
- Tomika.

00:56.467 --> 00:57.400
Tomika.

00:57.400 --> 00:59.100
- [screeches]
- Oh!

00:59.100 --> 01:01.533
Tomika.
- Okay.

01:01.533 --> 01:04.367
- What's going on?
Why are you hiding back there?

01:04.367 --> 01:07.300
- Some of us don't need
to draw attention to ourselves.

01:07.300 --> 01:09.700
- Summer
on the tambourine!

01:09.700 --> 01:12.167
Check it out.
I'm literally on the tambourine.

01:12.167 --> 01:14.833
Ha!

01:14.833 --> 01:17.200
- And some of us do.

01:17.200 --> 01:19.500
- Come on, Tomika,
get into it.

01:19.500 --> 01:22.633
A-all the rock legends have
their signature moves.

01:22.633 --> 01:25.467
Uh, Mick Jagger has
his Rooster Strut.

01:27.067 --> 01:28.833
And Miley Cyrus has
her twerk.

01:28.833 --> 01:30.867
- Okay.
- Mm.

01:30.867 --> 01:34.133
- And Dewey Finn has
the Speaker Straddle.

01:34.133 --> 01:37.333
- If it keeps you from twerking,
go for it.

01:37.333 --> 01:39.500
- It's a move I created
for my short-lived

01:39.500 --> 01:42.633
and poorly-named band,
The Everlasting.

01:42.633 --> 01:44.400
- Careful, Mr. Finn.

01:44.400 --> 01:47.067
- Chillax, I'm just trying
to prove a point

01:47.067 --> 01:48.867
about showmanship
to Tomika.

01:48.867 --> 01:51.233
[all yelling]

01:51.233 --> 01:53.367
all: Mr. Finn!
- Oh!

01:56.300 --> 01:59.067
- Uh, I think
I've made my point.

01:59.067 --> 02:00.100
- [grunts]

02:00.100 --> 02:01.733
- [groans]

02:01.733 --> 02:04.767
- * Stop tellin' me
to read between the lines *

02:04.767 --> 02:07.333
* It all adds up
to one thing *

02:07.333 --> 02:08.933
- Five, four, three,
two, one.

02:08.933 --> 02:11.467
- * If you think you're gonna
lose your cool *

02:11.467 --> 02:14.100
* Well, sometimes you gotta
break the rules *

02:14.100 --> 02:16.867
* Hey, show me what you know,
give it up to rock 'n' roll *

02:16.867 --> 02:18.667
* 'Cause we ain't
gonna stop *

02:18.667 --> 02:20.200
*

02:20.200 --> 02:22.300
* If you're feeling like
you're gettin' schooled *

02:22.300 --> 02:24.800
* There's an answer
right in front of you *

02:24.800 --> 02:27.500
* Hey, show me what you know,
give it up to rock 'n' roll *

02:27.500 --> 02:29.200
* 'Cause we ain't
gonna stop *

02:29.200 --> 02:31.433
- * Hey!
- * Are you ready to rock?

02:33.867 --> 02:35.833
[rock music]

02:35.833 --> 02:39.633
- Tomika, wait.
Wait up.

02:39.633 --> 02:41.767
- Still hurting
from your fall?

02:41.767 --> 02:43.833
- Fall?
I don't recall any fall,

02:43.833 --> 02:46.733
just a killer rock move
that I totally meant to do.

02:46.733 --> 02:49.400
Tomika, you're usually
so confident when you play,

02:49.400 --> 02:50.700
and we need you to be
at your best

02:50.700 --> 02:52.433
if we're going to win
Battle of the Bands.

02:52.433 --> 02:54.467
What's going on?

02:54.467 --> 02:56.167
- My brothers filmed me
practicing at home

02:56.167 --> 02:57.500
and put it
on the Internet.

02:57.500 --> 03:00.267
It turns out I make funny faces
when I play.

03:00.267 --> 03:03.400
- All the great basses
suffer from bass face.

03:03.400 --> 03:06.300
I bet you look cool.

03:06.300 --> 03:08.100
[goat bleating effect]

03:08.100 --> 03:09.667
I was insanely wrong.

03:11.067 --> 03:12.333
Who cares?

03:12.333 --> 03:14.533
- They made another one.

03:14.533 --> 03:15.733
[elephant trumpeting effect]

03:15.733 --> 03:17.600
- [giggles]

03:17.600 --> 03:19.400
That's not funny.

03:19.400 --> 03:21.767
- And this.

03:21.767 --> 03:23.600
[burping effect]

03:23.600 --> 03:28.067
- I can't believe you actually
came to school today.

03:28.067 --> 03:31.533
- Thanks, Mr. Finn.
You're a sensitive soul.

03:31.533 --> 03:33.967
- So your brothers made
a dumb video.

03:33.967 --> 03:35.733
- It's not the video.
It's not even

03:35.733 --> 03:37.667
that all my brothers' friends
have seen it.

03:37.667 --> 03:40.067
It's that this is
how I look when I play,

03:40.067 --> 03:41.833
like a total doofus.

03:41.833 --> 03:43.900
I can't let people see me
that way anymore.

03:43.900 --> 03:46.300
- [scoffs]
My point is you're fearless

03:46.300 --> 03:49.067
on the skateboard.
Bring that to your rock.

03:49.067 --> 03:50.467
Who's your favorite artist?

03:50.467 --> 03:52.633
- I'm totally
into Demi Lovato.

03:52.633 --> 03:55.233
- Perfect.
Demi Lovato was shy,

03:55.233 --> 03:56.633
but when she got
onstage,

03:56.633 --> 03:59.267
she transformed herself
into a confident rocker.

03:59.267 --> 04:02.700
Now she owns it.
Be like her.

04:02.700 --> 04:04.400
- I don't know
if I can do it.

04:04.400 --> 04:07.333
- Trust me, Tomika.
I know Demi Lovato--

04:07.333 --> 04:11.200
- Wh--really?
You know Demi Lovato?

04:11.200 --> 04:12.533
- Well, I meant that--

04:12.533 --> 04:14.367
- That is so cool!

04:14.367 --> 04:16.067
- It is?

04:16.067 --> 04:19.567
Yeah, it is cool that
I know Demi Lovato.

04:19.567 --> 04:23.567
So are you gonna start rocking
like Demi Lovato?

04:23.567 --> 04:26.067
Who I totally know.

04:26.067 --> 04:27.567
- I guess I can try.

04:27.567 --> 04:29.600
- That's the spirit.
I'm gonna call Demi

04:29.600 --> 04:31.767
and tell her
all about you.

04:31.767 --> 04:34.700
- [squeals]

04:36.100 --> 04:39.067
- Who is Demi Lovato?

04:39.067 --> 04:42.067
[rock music]

04:42.067 --> 04:43.167
*

04:43.167 --> 04:46.333
- Whoa.
Cool new style.

04:46.333 --> 04:47.567
- Thanks, Zack.

04:47.567 --> 04:51.100
I went with the superhero
underwear today.

04:51.100 --> 04:53.433
- We can't actually see
your underwear.

04:53.433 --> 04:55.933
- You can see it
in my confident strut.

04:57.833 --> 04:59.400
- Hey, Summer.

04:59.400 --> 05:01.533
- Tomika,
I love your hair.

05:01.533 --> 05:03.767
- Thanks.
I've decided to stop hiding

05:03.767 --> 05:05.767
and be more like my hero,
Demi Lovato.

05:05.767 --> 05:09.600
- Well, it's working.
You look like a total rock star.

05:09.600 --> 05:11.200
I wish I could
pull that off.

05:11.200 --> 05:14.067
- You can.
Pull.

05:15.500 --> 05:16.567
- [laughs]

05:16.567 --> 05:19.067
- You just got
rock-star-ed.

05:19.067 --> 05:23.767
* You make me...
both: * Glo-o-ow

05:23.767 --> 05:29.467
* But I cover up
won't let it sho-o-ow *

05:29.467 --> 05:31.400
* So I--

05:31.400 --> 05:34.533
[rock music]

05:36.900 --> 05:39.867
- Well, it says here
I was wrong.

05:39.867 --> 05:42.633
Lightning is actually frozen
moisture colliding,

05:42.633 --> 05:44.100
creating a static charge,

05:44.100 --> 05:46.533
and not, as I had
previously stated,

05:46.533 --> 05:48.867
two angels
in a fist fight.

05:48.867 --> 05:50.500
Hmm.

05:50.500 --> 05:54.467
Oh, let's put the books away
and hit The Rolling Stones hard.

05:55.867 --> 05:58.967
- Guys, I was thinking
that maybe

05:58.967 --> 06:00.500
instead of playing
"Under My Thumb,"

06:00.500 --> 06:02.100
we could change it up
a little bit.

06:02.100 --> 06:03.433
- Oh, What's this?

06:03.433 --> 06:05.533
- Sheet music for Demi Lovato's
"Heart Attack."

06:05.533 --> 06:07.167
- Sweet!

06:07.167 --> 06:10.200
Wait, it's cool for dudes
to like Demi Lovato, right?

06:10.200 --> 06:11.200
- Yeah.

06:11.200 --> 06:13.300
- Sweet!

06:13.300 --> 06:15.933
- If it makes Tomika look good,
it makes the band look good.

06:15.933 --> 06:19.500
Me, I look good
either way.

06:19.500 --> 06:21.067
- Let's do this.

06:21.067 --> 06:23.633
- Yeah!
My booty's ready to jam.

06:23.633 --> 06:25.733
[keyboard flourish]

06:25.733 --> 06:29.233
- Thanks, guys.
Follow my lead.

06:29.233 --> 06:31.067
- Let's do this!

06:31.067 --> 06:34.967
- * So I'm
puttin' my defenses up *

06:34.967 --> 06:37.900
* 'Cause I don't wanna
fall in love *

06:37.900 --> 06:39.233
* If I ever did that

06:39.233 --> 06:42.600
* I think I'd have
a heart attack *

06:42.600 --> 06:44.633
[all cheering]
- [laughs]

06:44.633 --> 06:46.867
That's what I've been
looking for.

06:46.867 --> 06:48.867
- Tomika, you kicked
that song's butt.

06:48.867 --> 06:51.667
- All I needed to do was
be more like Demi.

06:51.667 --> 06:54.500
Maybe you could take a video
of us and send it to her.

06:54.500 --> 06:56.600
Mr. Finn is friends
with Demi Lovato.

06:56.600 --> 06:59.467
- What?
- No way, that's so cool!

06:59.467 --> 07:00.833
- My mom knows the guy

07:00.833 --> 07:02.133
from the light-up slippers
commercial.

07:02.133 --> 07:03.600
- Oh, the guy
with the slippers?

07:03.600 --> 07:06.233
- No, the one who falls
down the stairs.

07:07.600 --> 07:10.067
- Wait, do you actually
hang out with her?

07:10.067 --> 07:14.233
- Uh, sure, you know,
whenever she's in town.

07:14.233 --> 07:16.400
- Demi Lovato's in town
this week.

07:16.400 --> 07:18.767
- We're in town this week!

07:18.767 --> 07:20.067
- No way.
She is?

07:20.067 --> 07:22.067
- Yeah, she's playing
Texas Memorial.

07:22.067 --> 07:25.767
- She is.
I knew that.

07:25.767 --> 07:27.633
- Mr. Finn, get her
to come see us play.

07:27.633 --> 07:31.067
- That would be the coolest
thing you've ever done!

07:31.067 --> 07:32.100
Can you?

07:32.100 --> 07:33.267
- Yeah, I can do

07:33.267 --> 07:34.900
the coolest thing
I've ever done.

07:34.900 --> 07:37.300
- Yeah!
- Man, no reason to believe

07:37.300 --> 07:39.233
this isn't gonna happen.

07:41.300 --> 07:44.233
[rock music]

07:47.300 --> 07:48.700
- [clears throat]

07:48.700 --> 07:50.933
- Welcome to the Saint Teresa
Hotel, can I help you?

07:50.933 --> 07:52.833
- Hi, I'm friends
with Demi Lovato,

07:52.833 --> 07:54.067
but I forgot
her room number.

07:54.067 --> 07:55.933
Could you please
give it to me?

07:55.933 --> 07:57.733
- I'm sorry,
I'm not allowed to give out

07:57.733 --> 08:00.100
guests' personal
information.

08:00.100 --> 08:03.067
- Mm.

08:05.133 --> 08:06.167
How about now?

08:07.900 --> 08:12.633
- Sir, this is a prescription
for a fungal medicine.

08:12.633 --> 08:14.967
- I'm gonna need that.

08:14.967 --> 08:16.833
Come on, man,
what's the room number?

08:16.833 --> 08:18.133
- Mr. Finn?

08:18.133 --> 08:20.067
- Lawrence,
what are you doing here?

08:20.067 --> 08:22.067
- Our house is being
fumigated for termites,

08:22.067 --> 08:23.400
so we're staying here.

08:23.400 --> 08:25.067
- I'm sorry about that.

08:25.067 --> 08:26.900
- No, it's the best thing
that ever happened to me.

08:26.900 --> 08:28.167
They give you
a free robe,

08:28.167 --> 08:29.900
and you get a new shampoo
every day

08:29.900 --> 08:32.733
whether you take a shower
or not.

08:32.733 --> 08:36.100
Want some?
- No--pomegranate?

08:36.100 --> 08:37.833
- What are you doing here?

08:37.833 --> 08:38.933
- I'm trying to figure out

08:38.933 --> 08:41.400
what room my friend
is staying in.

08:41.400 --> 08:43.433
- I'm in 812.

08:43.433 --> 08:46.233
- Lawrence, don't you have
anything better to do?

08:46.233 --> 08:47.800
- No.
I've got 15 minutes

08:47.800 --> 08:49.800
until my mom and I have
our couples massage.

08:49.800 --> 08:52.067
- Hmm.
- Sir, there's no one

08:52.067 --> 08:54.067
under the name
Demi Lovato.

08:54.067 --> 08:56.733
- She's obviously using
a fake name

08:56.733 --> 08:59.833
so regular fans,
not close friends like me,

08:59.833 --> 09:02.133
don't bug her.
I'll have to guess.

09:02.133 --> 09:04.600
- You're her friend; why
don't you call her and ask her?

09:04.600 --> 09:05.900
- More fun to guess.

09:05.900 --> 09:09.267
Is there a "Demi Roboto"
staying here?

09:09.267 --> 09:11.633
- No one's checked in
under that name.

09:11.633 --> 09:13.067
- How about "Lemi Cravato"?
- Nope.

09:13.067 --> 09:14.367
- "Stemmy Avocado"?
- No.

09:14.367 --> 09:17.067
- Marjorie Weinstein?
I like this game.

09:17.067 --> 09:18.600
- Stop acting silly.

09:18.600 --> 09:19.867
"Cray Cray McFakeName"?

09:19.867 --> 09:21.300
- Security!

09:21.300 --> 09:23.867
- Security?
They said the shampoo's free.

09:23.867 --> 09:25.333
You're on your own,
Mr. Finn.

09:26.667 --> 09:28.533
[rock music]

09:28.533 --> 09:30.133
[playing Demi Lovato's
"Heart Attack"]

09:30.133 --> 09:32.967
- * Never put my love
out on the line *

09:32.967 --> 09:35.700
* Never said yes
to the right guy *

09:35.700 --> 09:37.567
No, hold on, hold on.

09:37.567 --> 09:41.400
It's pretty good,
but I think we can do better.

09:41.400 --> 09:45.200
- We've done it 15 times.
I love you,

09:45.200 --> 09:47.367
but Tambourine Summer
wants to hurt you.

09:47.367 --> 09:49.767
- We just need to work
a little harder

09:49.767 --> 09:51.800
to get Demi Lovato's sound.

09:51.800 --> 09:53.800
Zack, you need
more distortion,

09:53.800 --> 09:56.133
Freddy, hit those toms
with drama,

09:56.133 --> 09:58.067
and Lawrence,
you're too loud.

09:58.067 --> 09:59.733
- I'm not even playing.

09:59.733 --> 10:01.700
- I mean your breathing.

10:01.700 --> 10:03.533
- But I have to breathe.

10:03.533 --> 10:04.900
- Do you?

10:04.900 --> 10:06.500
- [inhales deeply]

10:06.500 --> 10:09.033
- Come on, Tomika,
we're trying our best.

10:09.033 --> 10:10.633
- Maybe it's our look.

10:10.633 --> 10:13.800
Demi's band wears cool outfits
and disco ball helmets,

10:13.800 --> 10:16.067
and in her video
she has wind machines,

10:16.067 --> 10:20.633
steam geysers,
and covers herself in ink.

10:20.633 --> 10:23.767
We would look so amazing
doing that.

10:25.200 --> 10:27.633
* Puttin' my defenses up *

10:27.633 --> 10:30.500
* 'Cause I don't wanna
fall in love *

10:30.500 --> 10:31.967
* If I ever did that

10:31.967 --> 10:35.433
* I think I'd have
a heart attack *

10:35.433 --> 10:40.000
* You make me glo-o-ow

10:40.000 --> 10:46.000
* But I cover up
won't let it sho-o-ow *

10:46.000 --> 10:50.100
* So I'm
puttin' my defenses up *

10:50.100 --> 10:52.833
* 'Cause I don't wanna
fall in love *

10:52.833 --> 10:54.333
* If I ever did that

10:54.333 --> 11:00.100
* I think I'd have
a heart atta-a-ack *

11:00.100 --> 11:05.833
* I think I'd have
a heart atta-a-ack *

11:05.833 --> 11:08.533
* I think I'd have
a heart attack *

11:13.100 --> 11:14.167
Let's just do that.

11:14.167 --> 11:17.400
- [gasping
and panting]

11:17.400 --> 11:19.733
Nope, gotta breathe.

11:19.733 --> 11:20.967
- Eh.

11:20.967 --> 11:24.067
[rock music]

11:24.067 --> 11:26.867
- [laughs]
Dude, you look ridiculous.

11:26.867 --> 11:30.267
- You're wearing
the same thing.

11:30.267 --> 11:32.433
- Oh, yeah.

11:32.433 --> 11:34.900
- Come on, guys, I think
these helmets look cool.

11:34.900 --> 11:36.333
I look like a disco cop.

11:36.333 --> 11:40.533
You have the right to remain...
dancing! Ah!

11:40.533 --> 11:41.600
- Where's Tomika?

11:41.600 --> 11:43.367
[horror movie music]

11:43.367 --> 11:46.300
[water splashing]

11:46.300 --> 11:47.867
- I really hope
that's Tomika.

11:47.867 --> 11:50.300
I saw a horror movie
about giant sewer rats

11:50.300 --> 11:52.767
and it did not end well
for anyone.

11:54.800 --> 11:58.167
- Ready?
Here we go.

12:02.200 --> 12:05.200
- I think the wind machine
is set too high!

12:05.200 --> 12:06.200
- What?

12:06.200 --> 12:07.900
- I said I think
the wind machine

12:07.900 --> 12:09.433
is set too high!

12:09.433 --> 12:12.500
- The wind machine's
not set too high!

12:14.967 --> 12:17.233
It's perfect!

12:20.067 --> 12:23.233
[fast rock music]

12:23.233 --> 12:31.167
*

12:38.067 --> 12:40.500
- Whoo.
Okay,

12:40.500 --> 12:44.633
pretty good for our first try.
Let's do it again.

12:44.633 --> 12:46.867
- Are you nuts?

12:48.200 --> 12:50.567
- You're pushing us
too hard!

12:50.567 --> 12:54.067
- Demi Lovato's band
doesn't complain like this.

12:54.067 --> 12:57.067
- We're not her band!
We're School of Rock,

12:57.067 --> 12:58.967
and we're not comfortable
doing this.

13:00.233 --> 13:01.833
Or that.

13:01.833 --> 13:03.100
Or that.

13:04.800 --> 13:07.167
- Tomika,
this is too much.

13:07.167 --> 13:09.533
- We're not
at the Lovato level yet.

13:09.533 --> 13:11.933
I'm just trying
to make us better.

13:11.933 --> 13:13.567
- This doesn't feel
better to me.

13:13.567 --> 13:15.500
Look what you've done
to my hair.

13:17.200 --> 13:20.367
Phew!
Fixed it.

13:20.367 --> 13:22.167
- Fine.
You guys don't deserve

13:22.167 --> 13:23.967
to play a song
as great as "Heart Attack."

13:23.967 --> 13:25.167
I'm outta here.

13:25.167 --> 13:27.567
And I'm bringing my ink
with me.

13:27.567 --> 13:29.500
Mm-kay.

13:31.067 --> 13:34.433
[strains]

13:36.133 --> 13:37.533
I'll grab that later.

13:41.233 --> 13:44.367
- Tomika,
where are you--

13:46.100 --> 13:49.333
Look at this mess!

13:49.333 --> 13:52.467
We're all cleaning this up
right now.

13:54.233 --> 13:55.967
Hey, what's this remote control
doing here?

13:55.967 --> 13:57.500
- Mr. Finn, no!
- No!

14:03.067 --> 14:06.367
- Oh,
that's what that does.

14:10.267 --> 14:13.467
[rock music]

14:14.333 --> 14:15.800
- Any room for me?

14:15.800 --> 14:17.400
- It's kinda tight.
- Well, there's room

14:17.400 --> 14:20.167
if we just--
- Mm!

14:20.167 --> 14:22.367
- There's no room.
Sorry.

14:23.267 --> 14:26.433
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

14:26.433 --> 14:29.667
- Oh, I know
what's going on,

14:29.667 --> 14:32.100
and I think there's
an apology in order.

14:32.100 --> 14:33.433
- You mean it?

14:33.433 --> 14:35.233
- I told you guys
she'd come around.

14:35.233 --> 14:36.867
I'm so proud of you,
Tomeeks.

14:36.867 --> 14:38.667
- I accept your apology,

14:38.667 --> 14:42.067
and I forgive you all
for not being good enough.

14:42.067 --> 14:43.333
- Less proud.

14:43.333 --> 14:45.533
- You forgive us?

14:45.533 --> 14:47.933
- Of course.
So we're good, right?

14:47.933 --> 14:49.633
I can sit at the table?

14:49.633 --> 14:50.800
- You sure can.

14:54.967 --> 14:56.833
- Guys,
when you have a plan

14:56.833 --> 14:59.167
that everybody's
supposed to leave,

14:59.167 --> 15:02.200
you're supposed to tell
everybody!

15:02.200 --> 15:03.800
This is really embarrassing.

15:07.433 --> 15:09.933
- So we're not good.

15:09.933 --> 15:12.233
[rock music]

15:13.733 --> 15:15.467
- Mr. Finn,
can I talk to you?

15:15.467 --> 15:17.400
- Is it important?
Because I'm on my way

15:17.400 --> 15:18.733
to the men's room.

15:18.733 --> 15:21.800
- It's just I'm so upset.

15:21.800 --> 15:23.700
- All right.

15:23.700 --> 15:26.500
- I don't understand why
everyone is so mad at me.

15:26.500 --> 15:29.333
- Look, you've been
riding the band pretty hard.

15:29.333 --> 15:31.867
People get kicked out
for that kind of a thing.

15:31.867 --> 15:33.367
- Really?

15:33.367 --> 15:36.200
- Maybe you're trying too hard
to be like Demi Lovato.

15:36.200 --> 15:38.433
- But you told me to.

15:38.433 --> 15:40.433
You said it would help me
be less self-conscious

15:40.433 --> 15:42.600
after my brothers made
that embarrassing video.

15:42.600 --> 15:44.800
And it does,
but I can't be Demi

15:44.800 --> 15:47.267
if the band won't be
Demi's band.

15:47.267 --> 15:49.567
- I didn't mean be
exactly like Demi.

15:49.567 --> 15:52.500
I meant be brave like her
but still be Tomika.

15:52.500 --> 15:55.433
Now if you'll excuse me,
I've really gotta go.

15:55.433 --> 15:58.167
- I guess I have been
pretty hard on the band.

15:58.167 --> 16:02.333
- Still talking, okay.
[chuckles]

16:02.333 --> 16:04.067
- I should talk to them.

16:04.067 --> 16:05.867
Thanks, Mr. Finn,
for being the one who--

16:05.867 --> 16:07.900
- Gotta go!

16:07.900 --> 16:09.267
Comin'--

16:09.267 --> 16:10.833
- Oh, Mr. Finn,
may I have a moment?

16:10.833 --> 16:12.267
- No.

16:12.267 --> 16:15.867
[rock music]

16:15.867 --> 16:17.933
- Guys, I figured out
what's going on with Tomika.

16:17.933 --> 16:20.333
She's being tough
because she's scared.

16:20.333 --> 16:22.667
- Scared?
She's not scared of anything.

16:22.667 --> 16:26.133
I've seen Tomika grind a rail
down a 50-foot staircase.

16:26.133 --> 16:30.100
- I've seen her go swimming
three minutes after she's eaten.

16:30.100 --> 16:32.633
She's insane!

16:32.633 --> 16:35.400
- Well, she's scared
of looking dumb onstage.

16:35.400 --> 16:39.100
- What, her bass face?
Big deal. [scoffs]

16:39.100 --> 16:40.100
[goat bleating effect]

16:40.100 --> 16:41.700
all: Whoa.

16:41.700 --> 16:43.333
- Yeah.

16:43.333 --> 16:44.933
- That still doesn't give her
the right to push us around.

16:44.933 --> 16:46.067
Right, Zack?

16:46.067 --> 16:48.633
- Huh?
Oh, I wasn't listening.

16:48.633 --> 16:52.367
I'm a little freaked out
by goats.

16:52.367 --> 16:55.233
One ate my pants
at a petting zoo.

16:56.533 --> 16:59.667
- Okay, I'll admit it,
she was out of line.

16:59.667 --> 17:01.067
So now we have
a choice.

17:01.067 --> 17:03.567
We either help Tomika
with her problem,

17:03.567 --> 17:06.600
or we tell her to find
another band.

17:09.167 --> 17:11.600
- So you're telling me
if a goat was here right now,

17:11.600 --> 17:13.267
none of you would be
freaked out?

17:15.067 --> 17:18.067
[rock music]

17:18.067 --> 17:21.400
*

17:22.833 --> 17:24.633
- [sighs]

17:24.633 --> 17:26.333
[playing rock music]
Guys, I'm sorry

17:26.333 --> 17:27.867
for how I treated
you all.

17:27.867 --> 17:29.900
I guess--

17:29.900 --> 17:31.133
What's going on?

17:31.133 --> 17:32.700
- Uh, well,
we were just--

17:32.700 --> 17:34.733
- Rehearsing.
Rehearsing without me.

17:34.733 --> 17:37.067
- No--
I mean, yeah, but--

17:37.067 --> 17:40.200
- So I've been kicked out
of the band for being too tough?

17:40.200 --> 17:41.367
Fine.

17:41.367 --> 17:44.367
- No, wait.

17:44.367 --> 17:46.067
Tomika, wait,
come back.

17:46.067 --> 17:48.267
- What's the point?
It's too late.

17:48.267 --> 17:50.400
I know the band
hates me.

17:50.400 --> 17:51.867
- We don't hate you.

17:51.867 --> 17:53.667
The reason we held practice
without you

17:53.667 --> 17:56.467
is because we were
rehearsing your song.

17:56.467 --> 17:58.067
We really wanted
to get it right.

17:58.067 --> 18:02.600
And not as Demi Lovato's band,
but as us.

18:02.600 --> 18:05.800
[playing Demi Lovato's
"Heart Attack"]

18:05.800 --> 18:13.733
*

18:15.433 --> 18:17.267
[song ends]

18:17.267 --> 18:18.433
[both chuckle]

18:18.433 --> 18:20.533
- You sound amazing.

18:20.533 --> 18:22.433
You guys did this for me?

18:22.433 --> 18:24.233
- We'd do anything for you.

18:24.233 --> 18:27.367
- That's it,
we've had it up to here!

18:28.933 --> 18:30.433
Let's go, guys.

18:33.300 --> 18:35.400
Are we not doing this?

18:36.300 --> 18:38.367
We spend all day together.

18:38.367 --> 18:40.633
How hard is it
to keep me in the loop?

18:42.833 --> 18:46.667
- Thanks, guys.
I really appreciate this.

18:46.667 --> 18:49.967
And I'm sorry I got
out of control.

18:49.967 --> 18:52.167
- Well?

18:52.167 --> 18:55.333
- Let's do this.

